        <Description>This image is a composite of separate exposures acquired by the Hubble Space Telescope using the ACS/WFC instrument. Several filters were used to sample specific wavelength ranges. The color results from assigning different hues (colors) to each monochromatic (grayscale) image associated with an individual filter. In this case, the assigned colors are:   Red = F814W Red = F656N Green = F555W Blue = F435W</Description>
        <Credits>NASA, ESA, and the Hubble Heritage (STScI/AURA)-ESA/Hubble Collaboration</Credits>
